{# Single humanized chip — shared by the Today and Review Queue cards.

   Renders one ``HumanFlag`` as a chip carrying:
     * the human title + brief detail as visible text,
     * the raw flag code in ``data-flag-code`` so workers can grep
       devtools when something looks wrong,
     * the raw code repeated in ``title`` so hovering surfaces the
       machine identifier.

   Severity band drives the chip color via ``hf.chip_class`` (set by
   ``aegis.web._flag_labels``): decline -> ``bad``, material -> ``warn``,
   look_closer -> ``info``, context -> bare ``chip``.

   Inputs:
     - hf: HumanFlag (in scope from the calling for-loop)
#}
<span class="chip {{ hf.chip_class }}" data-flag-code="{{ hf.code }}" title="{{ hf.code }}">{{ hf.title }}{% if hf.detail %} <span class="chip-detail">· {{ hf.detail }}</span>{% endif %}</span>
